body:
I got a assert error during compilation when a void function is called from some certain tasks and functions in my code.  I can't generalize where this happens but here's a small example.

```systemverilog
module test;

  initial begin
    v1;
    v2;
    $finish;
  end

  function void v1;
    $display("v1 is called");
    v2;  // this is not OK
  endfunction

  function void v2;
    $display("v2 is called");
    //v1;  // this is OK
  endfunction

endmodule
```
This is the error message from running "iverilog -g2012 *.v":

> void_func.v:11: assert: elaborate.cc:3838: failed assertion dscope->elab_stage() >= 3
> sh: line 1: 3905250 Done                    /usr/local/lib/ivl/ivlpp -L -F"/tmp/ivrlg25058eb2e" -f"/tmp/ivrlg5058eb2e" -p"/tmp/ivrli5058eb2e"
>      3905251 Aborted                 (core dumped) | /usr/local/lib/ivl/ivl -C"/tmp/ivrlh5058eb2e" -C"/usr/local/lib/ivl/vvp.conf"


So, v1 can't call v2.  However, v2 can call v1 fine (comment line 11 and uncomment line 16).
Also, If you remove 'void' from v2, it will compile OK, just with a warning that v2 is being called as a task.

